18:14.872 --> 18:20.599
We're told in the Bible that over 500 eyewitnesses saw him alive, but then he ascended back into heaven.

18:21.360 --> 18:24.024
And that's the moment that we're stepping into in Acts chapter two.

18:24.404 --> 18:27.448
His followers have gathered in Jerusalem for quite some time.

18:27.508 --> 18:35.418
They're praying and worshiping and asking many of the same questions that maybe we're asking today, what is God doing?

18:36.419 --> 18:38.482
Why am I here and what do I do next?

18:39.106 --> 18:42.791
Well, as disciples were gathered, we turn to Acts two, verse two.

18:43.773 --> 18:50.983
And it says, suddenly a sound like a blowing wind came from heaven and filled the whole house where they were sitting.

18:51.924 --> 18:58.653
So what's happening is the Holy Spirit, the undeniable presence of God starts to fill the room.

18:59.815 --> 19:05.303
