Peter goes on in verse 22, 23, and says, Jesus of Nazareth was a man accredited by God to you by miracles, wonders, and signs which God did among you through him.

20:16.097 --> 20:23.965
And he's saying, as you yourselves know, this man Jesus was handed over to you by God's deliberate plan and foreknowledge.

20:24.625 --> 20:30.812
And you with the help of wicked men put him to death by nailing him to the cross.

20:31.592 --> 20:33.234
Now that this crowd has

20:33.538 --> 20:36.061
gathered, he said, you've seen this guy.

20:37.002 --> 20:37.943
You saw him alive.

20:37.963 --> 20:40.586
You saw the teaching, the healing, the miracles.

20:40.626 --> 20:44.590
And you were maybe also there when he was crucified.

20:45.371 --> 20:50.757
Perhaps you were among the ones who were laughing, mocking, yelling to crucify him.

20:51.478 --> 21:02.770
Peter continues verse 24, but God raised Jesus from the dead, freeing him from the agony of death because it was impossible for death.

21:02.914 --> 21:04.135
to keep his hold on him.

21:04.936 --> 21:08.581
And then in verse 32, and we are all witnesses of it.

21:09.542 --> 21:10.463
It's been 50 days.

21:11.244 --> 21:13.887
He's saying, you saw Jesus alive even after he had died.

21:13.947 --> 21:17.191
You felt his power and his presence.

21:17.231 --> 21:18.352
You know what he has done.

21:18.392 --> 21:19.734
You know what he can do.

21:19.774 --> 21:27.403
And so Peter continues, God has made this Jesus, whom you crucified both Lord and Messiah.

21:28.424 --> 21:30.226
And when the people heard this, they were cut.

21:30.818 --> 21:33.741
to the heart, in other words, they felt like God was speaking right to them.

21:34.662 --> 21:38.387
Let me ask you, do you believe Jesus is who he says he is?

21:39.888 --> 21:47.237
Do you believe that Jesus was crucified and died so that you could receive the forgiveness of sin?

21:47.297 --> 21:53.764
Do you believe that he rose from the dead to prove that death does not get the final say?

21:54.706 --> 21:58.610
That through faith in him, we receive the promise of eternal life.

21:59.394 --> 22:04.982
Do you believe that Jesus now, through the Holy Spirit, lives within you and among us?

22:05.863 --> 22:06.424
And they did.

22:06.504 --> 22:13.554
In verse 37, they said to Peter and the other apostles, brothers, brothers, what shall we do?

22:13.634 --> 22:16.198
Peter replied, repent and be baptized.

22:16.318 --> 22:20.804
Every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins.

22:21.705 --> 22:25.010
So if you have put your faith in Jesus, whether that happens today,

22:25.122 --> 22:29.389
happened last month or years ago and you have not been baptized in our one job.

22:30.150 --> 22:33.835
Our next step as a follower of Jesus is to be baptized.

22:33.875 --> 22:34.677
That's what they did.

22:34.717 --> 22:41.167
Those who accepted his message were baptized and about 3,000 were added to their number that day.

22:41.207 --> 22:50.060
Almost every time in scripture, when someone believes and puts their trust, their faith in Jesus Christ, the very next step is baptism.

22:51.082 --> 22:53.906
So what is God saying to you right now?

22:54.818 --> 22:55.959
What shall you do?

22:56.940 --> 23:00.044
Well, let me give you three reasons why you should get baptized today.

23:00.064 --> 23:03.568
The first is delayed obedience is still disobedience.

23:03.628 --> 23:08.233
One of the most frustrating things about being a parent is when your kids say, I'll take care of it.

23:09.334 --> 23:10.315
When are you gonna clean your room?

23:10.375 --> 23:11.136
I'll take care of it.

23:11.717 --> 23:12.698
When are you gonna do the dishes?

23:12.858 --> 23:13.519
I'll take care of it.

23:13.539 --> 23:14.760
When are you gonna deal with that smell?

23:14.840 --> 23:15.941
Yeah, yeah, I'll take care of it.

23:16.782 --> 23:23.730
But as parents, what we quickly learn is that I'll take care of it could be in the next hour, the next day, or sometime in the next decade.

23:24.162 --> 23:33.335
So for everyone's sanity, kids, and honestly, for parents and adults too, we need a few clear deadlines and maybe a couple reminders.

23:34.396 --> 23:36.198
Same thing happens when it comes to baptism.

23:37.140 --> 23:41.926
Many of you have thought, yeah, one day, I'll take care of it.

23:41.946 --> 23:47.854
You believe in Jesus, you've committed to follow Him, but for some reason, when it comes to baptism, you've said someday, just not now.

23:48.976 --> 23:50.578
So, when?

23:51.362 --> 23:57.949
Let me lovingly say, today should be your day because delayed obedience is still disobedience.

23:57.969 --> 24:04.856
Now, one of the reasons that people hesitate, some people hesitate is because they were baptized as infants.

24:05.837 --> 24:10.222
But instead of letting that be a hindrance, can I encourage you be grateful?

24:11.283 --> 24:18.450
That means your parents cared enough about you to want you to be raised in faith, but Scripture also makes clear.

24:19.010 --> 24:25.737
that you should still be baptized once you're old enough to decide for yourself why a couple reasons.

24:25.837 --> 24:28.000
First, infants were never baptized in scripture.

24:29.001 --> 24:33.386
It was a practice that was introduced by the church in those first early centuries.

24:34.227 --> 24:43.277
And next, every baptism we see in the Bible happens after someone personally puts their faith in Jesus, meaning they were old enough to make a heart and mind decision.

24:44.138 --> 24:48.242
And last, the word for baptized in the Greek is this word baptism.

24:48.578 --> 24:51.942
which means to immerse, submerge, or dip.

24:52.903 --> 24:58.570
There's a spiritual reality to a willing person being fully immersed in water.

24:59.371 --> 25:00.052
Now to be clear.

25:00.733 --> 25:08.222
God knows that physical limitations exist, so if all you're able to do is have water poured on you.

25:08.262 --> 25:09.764
God is so much bigger than that.

25:10.705 --> 25:18.354
In fact, some of those powerful baptisms that I personally experience are those where people for a variety of reasons can only have water

25:18.466 --> 25:20.129
poured on them.

25:20.149 --> 25:27.644
But if any of those reasons resonate with you, even if you were baptized as an infant like me, again, be grateful.

25:27.704 --> 25:30.330
Just don't let it become a reason to delay obedience.

25:31.091 --> 25:38.486
I know we might have some concern about disappointing our family, but this step of baptism is ultimately about honoring God.

25:39.107 --> 25:40.690
So if you sense that nudge,

25:41.026 --> 25:46.834
That prompting, especially if you've never been baptized before, today is your day.

25:46.894 --> 25:47.795
You are here.

25:47.855 --> 25:50.419
We've got a pool right behind me.

25:50.479 --> 25:52.081
We're ready now for you.

25:52.101 --> 25:52.682
You're ready.

25:52.802 --> 25:53.283
Let's go.

25:53.323 --> 25:55.606
Okay, next point.

25:55.626 --> 25:56.948
Second reason to get baptized is this.

25:57.008 --> 26:00.172
Baptism is a public declaration of faith and salvation.

26:01.174 --> 26:10.066
Baptism is the act of declaring to friends, family, the world, and ultimately God that you have been

26:10.338 --> 26:13.663
Saved baptism does not save a person.

26:14.544 --> 26:18.349
So begs the question, what does save a person?

26:19.010 --> 26:21.313
Well, it's faith in Christ, period.

26:22.134 --> 26:33.931
And before we go any further, I understand that some of us may not fully comprehend what it means to have faith in Jesus or what the gospel truly is.

26:33.971 --> 26:39.378
And I want to make sure we all know because it's really good news.

26:39.842 --> 26:41.504
And I want to make sure you understand.

26:42.285 --> 26:49.313
However, before we can fully understand the good news, we also have to understand the bad news.

26:50.033 --> 26:50.995
And here is the bad news.

26:51.836 --> 26:56.821
Romans 3.23 says, all have sinned and fallen short of God's standard.

26:57.662 --> 26:59.524
Most of us would not argue with that.

27:00.225 --> 27:04.890
We lie, we deceive, we lose our patience, we yell bad things at the TV.

27:05.571 --> 27:08.274
When the Super Bowl winning quarterback could have been ours,

27:08.514 --> 27:09.995
We get really frustrated with that.

27:11.737 --> 27:13.038
And what does that sin earn us?

27:14.279 --> 27:16.802
Romans 6, 23 says, for the wages of sin is death.

27:16.822 --> 27:18.684
A wage is something we earn.

27:19.484 --> 27:23.308
The Bible says what we've earned because of our sin is death.

27:24.089 --> 27:27.171
And ultimately, that means separation from a holy God.

27:27.191 --> 27:28.212
God is perfect.

27:28.673 --> 27:30.214
And sin has to be dealt with.

27:31.175 --> 27:31.916
That's bad news.

27:32.957 --> 27:34.198
That brings us to the good news.

27:35.179 --> 27:38.482
Romans 5, 8 says, God demonstrates His own love for us in this.

27:38.562 --> 27:41.586
While we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

27:42.627 --> 27:47.654
You and I deserve punishment for our sin, but Jesus, He didn't deserve the punishment.

27:48.495 --> 27:49.276
He was sinless.

27:50.237 --> 27:52.801
And yet Jesus willingly gave up His life.

27:53.181 --> 27:54.703
Again, no one took it from Him.

27:55.064 --> 27:57.487
He did that to take the punishment that we deserved.

27:58.368 --> 28:01.232
He died in our place.

28:01.272 --> 28:06.098
One of the reason that people hesitate to get baptized is because they think they got to take care of all the sin.

28:06.626 --> 28:08.349
I've just got too much sin in my life.

28:08.549 --> 28:12.055
I've got to be sinless before I step into those baptism waters, but here's the truth.

28:12.416 --> 28:14.700
While we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

28:15.501 --> 28:19.468
That means while we were still sinners, you can step into these baptism waters.

28:20.349 --> 28:29.124
In Romans 10, 9, it concludes as if you confess with your mouth and believe in your heart that God raised Jesus from the dead, you will be saved.

28:29.184 --> 28:32.530
Again, you are not saved by being good enough.

28:33.634 --> 28:35.476
by checking the religious boxes.

28:35.516 --> 28:36.537
You're not saved by that.

28:36.557 --> 28:39.620
You're not saved by stepping into these baptism waters.

28:39.680 --> 28:41.341
No, the Bible is crystal clear.

28:41.401 --> 28:43.543
There is one way to be saved.

28:44.424 --> 28:48.068
It's by placing your faith, your trust in Jesus Christ.

28:48.929 --> 28:55.535
It's believing that He died in your place to pay the penalty for your sin that you deserve.

28:56.376 --> 29:02.962
