29:03.138 --> 29:03.939
of our days.

29:04.019 --> 29:05.782
So let me ask you, have you done that?

29:07.425 --> 29:09.108
Have you put your faith in Jesus?

29:09.148 --> 29:12.433
Have you decided to make him Lord and King of your life?

29:12.614 --> 29:22.670
If you haven't, I'm gonna give you an opportunity in just a few moments just to confess with your mouth and believe in your heart to pray along silently with me.

29:23.311 --> 29:30.002
But if you're someone who's already put your faith in Jesus while your salvation is secure, this next step of baptism, it's not

29:30.850 --> 29:33.574
It's not a suggestion, it's not optional.

29:33.674 --> 29:37.380
In fact, it's a teaching, a command found all throughout scripture.

29:37.420 --> 29:41.707
It comes with this assumption that baptism always accompanied faith in Jesus.

29:42.709 --> 29:52.264
As Jason taught last week, Jesus' great commission to all of his followers was this in Matthew 28 and 19, therefore go and make disciples.

29:53.265 --> 29:56.210
Disciples is someone who follows in the footsteps of Jesus.

29:56.738 --> 29:58.681
Are you a disciple and are you making disciples?

29:58.721 --> 30:04.570
This says of all nations, every tongue, every tribe, every ethnicity, all people are created in the image of God.

30:04.890 --> 30:09.237
This is baptizing them in the name of the Father, the Son of the Holy Spirit.

30:09.537 --> 30:11.280
Baptism is part of that great commission.

30:12.302 --> 30:12.722
I get it.

30:12.742 --> 30:17.529
If you're not a Christian, baptism can appear to be one of the weirder things we do, all right?

30:18.210 --> 30:20.995
Well, why are all these people going in and out of the water?

30:21.435 --> 30:22.757
What are my friends gonna think?

30:22.777 --> 30:24.180
What's my family gonna say?

30:24.300 --> 30:25.842
