30:26.402 --> 30:28.185
I've been a Christian for quite a long time.

30:28.205 --> 30:30.688
I want to be weird if I get baptized now.

30:31.629 --> 30:34.293
People might think I should have done this years ago.

30:34.333 --> 30:36.657
And let me just set you free.

30:36.737 --> 30:38.760
Nobody will be thinking that.

30:39.601 --> 30:43.707
Everyone here and online will only be celebrating with you.

30:43.747 --> 30:51.698
So if God has changed your life, if you've experienced the hope of Jesus Christ,

30:52.610 --> 31:05.890
If Jesus has done something in you that you just can't deny then today, an obedience to Jesus, your step is to publicly declare your faith and salvation through baptism.

31:06.251 --> 31:07.192
Take the bold step.

31:08.094 --> 31:14.303
Third and final reason to get baptized today is it's time to remove what's holding you back.

31:15.645 --> 31:21.234
Is there something in you that is blocking your ability

31:21.730 --> 31:24.354
to really understand God's invitation.

31:25.496 --> 31:35.952
Or maybe another question is, there's something that's blocking your ability to experience complete freedom in Christ, not perfection, but more freedom.

31:36.994 --> 31:47.730
Hebrews 12.1 says, therefore, since we are surrounded by such a great cloud of witnesses, let us throw off everything that hinders in the sin that so easily intangles.

31:48.258 --> 31:53.165
What if this was the step that you needed to take to finally throw off what's been holding you back?

31:53.986 --> 32:04.640
What if today was the day that you allowed God to remove the weight, the power of that sin, the fear, the shame by taking the step of obedience through baptism?

32:05.522 --> 32:08.005
Look how Paul describes baptism in Romans 6.

32:08.045 --> 32:14.674
He says, don't you know that all of us who were baptized into Christ Jesus were baptized into his death?

32:16.098 --> 32:19.304
We were therefore buried with him through baptism into death.

32:19.805 --> 32:31.485
In order that, catch this, just as Christ was raised from the dead through the glory of the Father, we too may live a new life.

32:32.587 --> 32:39.419
Paul is saying here is that baptism is a powerful symbol of what Jesus has already done for us through faith.

32:40.421 --> 32:41.202
When we go

32:41.410 --> 32:46.358
Under the water, it symbolizes that our sin has been buried with Christ.

32:47.760 --> 32:49.924
The power of that sin no longer owns us.

32:51.005 --> 33:01.863
And then when we rise up out of the water, it symbolizes that we have been raised to new life, washed clean, given a fresh start, empowered to a new future.

33:03.005 --> 33:08.754
Not because we are good, not because we'll never sin again, but because of Jesus.

33:09.538 --> 33:12.581
He took our sin and gave us His righteousness.

33:13.462 --> 33:16.085
He paid the penalty that we deserve.

33:17.166 --> 33:24.635
And so through His death, burial, and resurrection, we are offered forgiveness, freedom, and new life.

33:25.956 --> 33:28.179
Maybe there's a sin that you struggle to overcome.

33:29.500 --> 33:32.964
Maybe there's a stronghold that just keeps pulling you backward.

33:34.105 --> 33:38.450
His fear, shame, maybe it's lust, addiction, regret.

33:38.690 --> 33:43.417
Maybe 2025, it's just a year you desperately wanna leave behind.

33:44.559 --> 33:48.304
And so let me say this as clearly and lovingly as I can.

33:48.364 --> 33:56.396
For some of you, the reason that you haven't experienced that kind of breakthrough yet, because you haven't taken the step of obedience.

33:57.598 --> 34:03.346
So what if today was the day that God would pour out his spirit on you in a fresh way?

34:04.258 --> 34:09.625
What if today was the day that you could mark as a significant spiritual moment in your life?

34:09.645 --> 34:16.134
What if today was the day that you could look back a year from now and say, that was a day that changed everything?

34:16.194 --> 34:16.915
What if today?

34:16.975 --> 34:19.118
Again, there's nothing magical about these waters.

34:20.359 --> 34:29.391
But there is something significant that happens in our relationship with God when we take this step of obedience and allow Him to remove whatever is holding us back.

34:30.232 --> 34:31.634
Just like Andy and Cassie.

34:32.386 --> 34:38.796
who decided to get baptized last year during this very same service and said, we walked through the door to the pool and up the ladder.

34:39.457 --> 34:42.361
When we entered the water, she said, I felt a calm come over me.

34:43.143 --> 34:44.064
This was meant to be.

34:44.104 --> 34:48.411
This is what we were supposed to do as husband and wife together.

34:48.771 --> 34:55.341
This is where we leave the darkest part of our lives and promise to work on us to bring Jesus into our lives more than ever.

34:56.563 --> 35:01.010
Or like Caitlin, who said she grew up praying to and worshiping the devil.

35:02.018 --> 35:06.663
But through her science class, she came to believe that God was the creator of the universe.

35:06.683 --> 35:18.456
So she picked up a Bible to learn what Jesus had to say, gave her life to him, and then last year she was baptized, along with her young son, pushing back against the darkness.

35:19.838 --> 35:22.581
Or Leon, who got baptized last year and said, I had no idea.

35:23.742 --> 35:24.883
My life was about to change.

35:24.943 --> 35:27.346
The moment I sat down, I felt this tug in my heart.

35:27.746 --> 35:32.053
I could feel the Holy Spirit almost take over my body as I tried to talk myself out of it.

35:32.633 --> 35:34.897
He said, I gave myself every excuse not to go.

35:34.917 --> 35:36.880
I even asked God for one more sign.

35:36.900 --> 35:44.011
I counted down from five in my head and at that exact moment, I felt a light squeeze in my wife's hand.

35:44.792 --> 35:51.883
From the moment I left my seat until I stepped into the water, it was the most spiritual thing I've ever experienced.

35:51.903 --> 35:56.690
Just like the crowd was asking in Acts two, what shall we do?

35:57.634 --> 36:03.421
Hands are there, repent, put your faith in Jesus and be baptized.

36:04.122 --> 36:06.725
So we're gonna give you a chance to do just that, just that.

36:07.766 --> 36:12.011
If you've never put your faith in Jesus before, I'm gonna lead you in a prayer just to pray along with me.

36:12.672 --> 36:19.280
But if you're someone who already has it and you haven't taken the step of baptism, again, you've heard me say it today is your day.

36:19.921 --> 36:20.642
There's no excuse.

36:21.483 --> 36:22.604
We've actually thought of everything.

36:23.305 --> 36:27.250
Clothes, towels, the water is actually quite warm, it feels lovely.

36:27.810 --> 36:28.611
We're ready for you.

36:30.072 --> 36:32.635
Now the only question is, will you take this step of obedience?

36:33.496 --> 36:37.920
So after we pray, we're gonna watch the story of Keegan, who took a similar step.

36:38.841 --> 36:42.845
And then your campus pastor is going to explain what happens next.

36:42.945 --> 36:48.830
But before I get there, if you're someone who isn't ready to take this step of baptism, please hear me also say, that's okay.

36:49.651 --> 36:56.658
But if you're ready to put your faith in Jesus, I would strongly urge you to prayerfully consider and text the word begin.

36:57.122 --> 37:03.811
to 77888 so we can give you some resources and help you follow Jesus in this journey of faith.

37:04.231 --> 37:04.772
Let's all pray.

37:06.153 --> 37:07.535
Heavenly Father, we love you.

37:08.376 --> 37:09.077
Man, we love you.

37:09.097 --> 37:09.978
I'm just so grateful.

37:10.239 --> 37:11.240
My heart is so full.

37:12.582 --> 37:14.064
The gospel is really good news.

37:15.005 --> 37:15.886
We don't deserve it.

37:16.847 --> 37:18.369
We haven't done anything to earn it.

37:18.489 --> 37:25.458
And yet you sent your son Jesus to die for us, to give us your righteousness.

37:27.074 --> 37:28.075
Thank you for that truth.

37:29.317 --> 37:36.545
For those who want to put their faith in Jesus, just pray silently along with me, Jesus, I'm putting my trust in you.

37:37.847 --> 37:39.028
I'm putting my faith in you.

37:39.048 --> 37:53.386
I don't even fully understand it, but what I want is to receive the forgiveness of my sin through what you accomplished on the cross, by the fact that you rose from the dead, overcame the grave.

37:54.367 --> 37:57.010
God, I receive the promise of eternal life.

37:57.922 --> 38:02.327
And I'm gonna do my best to follow you, to trust you, to obey you.

38:03.889 --> 38:05.411
I put my faith in you right now.

38:06.392 --> 38:11.619
And for everyone here, for those who are getting baptized, bless them, God, just what an obedient step.

38:11.679 --> 38:14.422
I pray there would be a moment in their lives that they would never forget.

38:14.442 --> 38:20.870
They would be reminded of the gospel truth that you have saved them by your grace through faith.

38:20.950 --> 38:25.176
There's nothing they can do to earn it and that they would experience real freedom.

38:25.196 --> 38:27.058
And for those who are still wondering,

38:27.298 --> 38:32.466
considering, God, I pray that you remove every excuse and let this be a day.

38:32.526 --> 38:38.335
They didn't expect to happen, but God, that they would step into these waters and choose to get baptized.

38:38.896 --> 38:40.518
Pray this all in Jesus' name.

38:41.159 --> 38:51.776
Amen.

38:52.076 --> 38:55.922
In the middle of the storm, you think you have it under control

38:56.002 --> 39:03.971
Everyone else around you's doing the same things you're doing, so it's all under control, but in reality, it really wasn't.

39:05.212 --> 39:06.113
I was out of control.

39:10.779 --> 39:12.240
Hi, my name is Keegan Rosette.

39:12.801 --> 39:14.283
I'm recovering alcoholic.

39:14.483 --> 39:16.025
I've been sober now for four years.

39:17.166 --> 39:19.228
I grew up in Inoka, Minnesota.

39:20.049 --> 39:24.434
My childhood dreams were to be a doctor and help people.

39:24.834 --> 39:34.665
From the outside looking in, I had a great image, you know, a kid growing up on a golf course, great house, great family, graduated with high honors.

39:34.825 --> 39:36.947
But there was a lot of pressures to succeed.

39:37.468 --> 39:39.350
In my youth, I was stubborn.

39:40.171 --> 39:44.576
I thought I had it all figured out and I didn't care what anyone else had to say about it.

39:49.281 --> 39:53.586
So after graduating high school, I got a golf scholarship to Morris.

39:53.986 --> 40:12.253
It's a very small town, rural community, and going from a graduating class of 650 people to a town that had what I felt like was no one, and the only way to meet people or partake in getting to know people was drinking.

40:14.356 --> 40:23.890
I lost kind of focus on my original goals of becoming a doctor, and I just fell into the wrong crowd really quickly.

40:24.098 --> 40:31.806
isolated and alone and I just realized I wasn't in a great place and so I transferred schools to Winona State.

40:32.367 --> 40:53.490
I felt an immediate connection once I got to Winona State but I quickly fell back into the trap of drinking you know Friday Saturday Sunday and just living for the weekend and oh man yeah it's waking up stressed and anxious shaky from the night before being hungover for

40:53.858 --> 40:55.460
more days out of the week than not.

40:56.281 --> 40:58.725
In my senior year, I got a DWI.

40:58.765 --> 41:02.069
That was probably what I thought was the worst of it all.

41:02.310 --> 41:04.853
But did that stop me from continuing to drink?

41:04.993 --> 41:06.796
No.

41:06.816 --> 41:12.323
The time for me when things really came to fruition was I was out with my brother.

41:12.784 --> 41:15.408
I couldn't even stand up on my own two feet at the time.

41:15.808 --> 41:18.952
Somehow I'd like passed out at the side of the police station.

41:19.593 --> 41:23.058
And I just remember waking up to these people in a

41:23.170 --> 41:25.553
asking if I needed to help in a ride home.

41:26.113 --> 41:29.797
And then the next day I was like, I can't keep doing this life.

41:29.877 --> 41:31.198
Like, this is getting old.

41:31.299 --> 41:32.800
I need some serious help.

41:33.080 --> 41:37.365
And so that was the day like I started making some serious changes in my life.

41:40.608 --> 41:49.778
There came a point probably five years ago where my mom was attending the Blaine campus and she just reached out to me and I said yes to going and

41:49.890 --> 41:56.517
I just remember going to Eaglebrook for the first time and crying, although my big behaviors didn't change initially.

41:56.537 --> 42:00.180
I think the seed was planted for something different.

42:01.622 --> 42:05.326
Four years ago, I started volunteering here at the Noka campus.

42:05.766 --> 42:07.508
I was an auditorium host.

42:07.888 --> 42:12.713
And so I got the opportunity to help out with a lot of the baptisms.

42:12.733 --> 42:16.137
And I quickly saw that the amazing experiences people were having.

42:16.197 --> 42:17.458
And I always felt this like,

42:17.570 --> 42:20.333
burning desire in my heart like, you should probably do this.

42:20.493 --> 42:22.435
But I just kept putting it off and off.

42:22.795 --> 42:30.502
But then this past baptism down at like Johanna, there was the opportunity to get baptized again.

42:34.206 --> 42:38.510
My girlfriend now, she was like, oh, you should probably do this.

42:38.570 --> 42:40.131
And I'm like, yeah, you're right.

42:40.331 --> 42:43.494
And lo and behold, I was asked to share my story.

42:43.534 --> 42:47.538
And yeah, I just couldn't turn this opportunity down.

42:47.874 --> 42:49.275
It was an amazing experience.

42:50.356 --> 42:52.539
I, of course, was, you know, nervous.

42:52.559 --> 42:56.502
I probably read my message a thousand times.

42:56.903 --> 43:02.628
But yeah, it just goes back to, you know, if you could just help one person, it made it all worth it.

43:08.274 --> 43:16.562
What I thought life was all about in my past, which is, you know, career, money, all the success is so much different now.

43:18.466 --> 43:20.608
Today, my life is filled with grace.

43:21.109 --> 43:25.174
God brought me a beautiful woman and her four beautiful children into my life.

43:25.794 --> 43:26.495
I pray daily.

43:27.076 --> 43:27.977
I'm in Bible study.

43:28.558 --> 43:29.278
I volunteer.

43:29.879 --> 43:32.162
I feel closer to God than I ever felt before.

43:33.043 --> 43:35.906
So, this baptism isn't just a symbol.

43:36.206 --> 43:40.091
It's a statement of surrender, of gratitude, of a new life.

43:40.571 --> 43:42.334
And I thank you all for being here to witness it.

43:42.674 --> 43:46.258
Let's go, baby!

43:47.106 --> 43:47.587
Thank you, Eric.

43:47.908 --> 43:51.258
Thank you for challenging me to step up to my comfort zone to God.

43:51.679 --> 43:54.528
Thank you for saving me and to anyone out there struggling.

43:55.170 --> 43:56.213
Don't give up on your dreams.

43:56.774 --> 44:00.505
God might have a different plan for you, but I promise it'll be better than on your own.

44:00.927 --> 44:02.130
So thank you.

44:04.610 --> 44:05.832
Hey everyone, my name's Jeff.

44:06.032 --> 44:09.999
I'm the online campus pastor and for some of you, it might not be too late.

44:10.219 --> 44:16.849
If a campus near you has another service, today could still be your day and it would be our honor to baptize you.

44:17.450 --> 44:27.346
You know, when people register to get baptized, we ask them to share the story of what brought them to this moment and one of my favorite traditions has been to sit down with a cup of coffee and just read through them.

44:27.458 --> 44:33.486
The backgrounds people come from, the circumstances they've gone through, the way that God has worked in their life.

44:33.686 --> 44:41.357
It is powerful stuff and it reminds me that God is still transforming lives of people every single day at our church.

44:41.497 --> 44:50.870
From elderly people coming to faith later in life to the massive amount of young people who have turned from the lie that culture tells them on how they should live.

44:51.270 --> 44:56.818
From elementary age kids who grew up with Christian parents who taught them how much Jesus loves them.

44:57.602 --> 45:07.571
Our hope for the rest of our time together is to capture the moment that all of their stories culminate, and they declare that they are followers of Jesus through baptism.

45:07.591 --> 45:11.442
Like it says in Romans 6, 3, that we were buried with Christ

45:11.618 --> 45:20.814
through baptism, in order that just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glory of the Father, that we might too walk in the newness of life.

45:20.914 --> 45:29.670
For if we have been united with Him in a death like His, we will certainly be united with Him in a resurrection like His.

45:30.111 --> 45:31.954
This is the gospel.

45:32.130 --> 45:35.578
And we get to watch it play out for the rest of our time together.

45:35.598 --> 45:41.292
And our goal is to give you just a glimpse of the scope of what is happening this weekend at our church.

45:41.633 --> 45:48.329
We're going to pop in from campus to campus and share some personal stories of those who are getting baptized.

45:48.349 --> 45:48.850
Here we go.

46:23.586 --> 46:23.988
Thank you.

48:02.178 --> 48:06.687
Just a moment, Mac is going to get baptized and I want to share with you some of his story.

48:07.188 --> 48:16.807
Mac grew up here at Eaglebrook going through our kids ministry, knowing about God and believing in him was normal and he had solid Christian parents who encouraged him in his faith.

48:16.907 --> 48:24.242
But later into his teens and early twenties, he was enticed by what our culture says will lead to a fulfilling life.

48:24.482 --> 48:28.187
He had a phrase that he would say that I believe in God, but I don't act like it.

48:28.568 --> 48:35.498
He chased after money and drugs and late into his teens, he got his girlfriend pregnant, and then he hit rock bottom.

48:35.878 --> 48:44.250
Overcome by his sin, feeling empty and stuck and at his lowest, his mom told him that God still loved him right where he was at.

48:44.791 --> 48:46.273
He felt like he couldn't accept it.

48:46.373 --> 48:52.882
He had been selfish and unlovable, made terrible choices that hurt everyone around him, and even in that place,

48:52.994 --> 48:57.826
God met him where he was and he took him from that place and brought him to where he is today.

48:58.627 --> 49:06.266
Far from perfect, but intentionally pursuing a deeper relationship with God and having his life transformed every single day.

49:06.707 --> 49:11.378
And today, Mac is declaring his faith by getting baptized.

53:05.506 --> 53:08.270
Courtney grew up in a very atheist household.

53:08.290 --> 53:11.735
No talk about God or faith, resistant to religion.

53:12.135 --> 53:17.203
Courtney lived out the only thing that she knew, which was pursuing what she thought would make her happy.

53:17.723 --> 53:23.692
She got pregnant and was engaged to be married, but as the date grew closer, they had a falling out.

53:23.712 --> 53:28.619
And this spiraled her into wanting to numb the pain with alcohol and drugs.

53:28.839 --> 53:33.746
And the father of her kids saw that she was struggling and invited her to church with him.

53:33.858 --> 53:47.995
She came to Eaglebrook and she loved it, bought her very own Bible, started reading about it, thinking about it, and about a year ago, Courtney became a follower of Jesus and her life has been totally transformed.

53:48.436 --> 53:52.781
And the person that invited her was Mac from the story that I told earlier.

53:53.302 --> 53:58.828
God is in the business of finding us wherever we are and bringing lost people back home.

53:59.209 --> 54:03.634
And today, Courtney is declaring her faith in Jesus by getting back home.

55:11.874 --> 55:16.160
Hey, thanks for hanging out this weekend and cheering on everyone who got baptized.

55:16.300 --> 55:19.405
Would you just join me as we close today's service and prayer?

55:20.426 --> 55:23.951
God, I thank you for what you're doing in the lives of so many people.

55:24.071 --> 55:26.635
I thank you for what you're doing here at our church.

55:26.655 --> 55:31.422
May we never grow tired of seeing the declaration of a changed life through baptism.

55:31.983 --> 55:35.167
May you be with every person who took that step this weekend.

55:35.428 --> 55:39.954
Would you be near to them, encouraging them, strengthening them and supporting them?

55:40.386 --> 55:49.321
Would you remind the rest of us of the commitment that we made to you, that we've died to our sin, that we've become alive in you through the power of your Holy Spirit?

55:49.922 --> 55:52.026
Thank you for your faithfulness in our lives.

55:52.086 --> 55:54.430
We love you, and in Jesus' name we pray.

55:54.490 --> 55:55.572
Amen.

55:56.053 --> 55:59.058
Well, hey, thanks for being with us, and we will see you next weekend.

